<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ISO-8859-1" ?>
<!DOCTYPE scenario SYSTEM "sipp.dtd">
<!--
  Long-call UAC for endurance: INVITE → 200 → ACK → OPTIONS-driven hold → BYE.

  After ACK the scenario loops on in-dialog OPTIONS from the B2BUA's
  keepaliveRule (TimerRules), replying 200 OK to EACH one for the life
  of the call — there is no per-call OPTIONS cap (see the loop comment
  below for why the former 4-iteration cap was removed: it produced a
  false ~130% long-call loss on every worker reboot by leaving the recv
  while the reclaim keepalive-replay burst was still arriving). The call
  terminates ONLY when keepalives stop (genuine teardown), which is the
  intended reboot-survival semantics. CurrentCall growth is bounded
  operationally by the job's `-l MAX_CONCURRENT` ceiling + `-recv_timeout`
  dead-call reaper (manifests/40-sipp-uac-job.yaml), not by an OPTIONS
  count — size those (and the offered LONG_CPS) for the target steady
  concurrency.

  The single exit path:
    - keepalive timeout (B2BUA torn down, chaos, network failure) →
      `recv timeout="420000" ontimeout="end_hold"` jumps to BYE.

  Earlier revisions used a flat `<pause milliseconds="1200000"/>` and
  relied on sipp's "default `pingreply` behavior" to auto-200 in-dialog
  OPTIONS during the pause. That was incorrect: sipp's `pingreply`
  only handles the legacy literal PING method, not OPTIONS. Every
  long-call therefore lost its A-leg keepalive, the B2BUA terminated
  the call ~5 min in, and the scenario's BYE 15 min later hit a dead
  dialog (481). See endurance run chaos-endurance-2h-20260511.

  Loop pattern mirrors `uas-basic.xml` (the B-leg UAS). 200 OK echoes
  `[last_From:]` / `[last_To:]` / `[last_Call-ID:]` / `[last_CSeq:]` so
  the response carries the dialog tags + CSeq from the request.

  The recv timeout is sized for the env-driven default
  `KEEPALIVE_INTERVAL_SEC=300s` (src/config/AppConfig.ts) — 420 s
  gives 120 s headroom. Under the reactive-only takeover model
  (ADR-0014) a quiescent long-call on a rebooting worker is recovered
  solely by the primary's bootstrap-rehydrate → ReclaimAll → smoothed
  keepalive replay; the worst-positioned quiescent call survives iff
  `reboot + smoothing_drain ≤ 120 s`. The embedded layer default is
  900 s; if a deployment uses the embedded layer with that larger
  interval, raise this timeout accordingly.

  RFC 3261 conformance:
    §11      In-dialog OPTIONS may be sent by either party; UAS
             responds 200 OK echoing dialog tags + CSeq.
    §12.2.1.1 In-dialog request CSeq increments within the dialog;
             sipp's 200 OK echoes the CSeq verbatim from the request.
-->
<scenario name="K8s UAC long-options — OPTIONS-driven hold; BYE on keepalive timeout">

  <send retrans="500">
    <![CDATA[
      INVITE sip:[service]@[remote_ip]:[remote_port] SIP/2.0
      Via: SIP/2.0/[transport] [local_ip]:[local_port];branch=[branch];rport
      From: sipp <sip:sipp@[local_ip]:[local_port]>;tag=[pid]SIPpTag00[call_number]
      To: sut <sip:[service]@[remote_ip]:[remote_port]>
      Call-ID: [call_id]
      CSeq: 1 INVITE
      X-Api-Call: {"destination":{"host":"[field0]","port":5060}}
      Contact: sip:sipp@[local_ip]:[local_port]
      Max-Forwards: 70
      Subject: K8s endurance long-call (OPTIONS keepalive)
      Resource-Priority: esnet.0
      Content-Type: application/sdp
      Content-Length: [len]

      v=0
      o=user1 53655765 2353687637 IN IP[local_ip_type] [local_ip]
      s=-
      c=IN IP[media_ip_type] [media_ip]
      t=0 0
      m=audio [media_port] RTP/AVP 0
      a=rtpmap:0 PCMU/8000
    ]]>
  </send>

  <recv response="100" optional="true"/>
  <recv response="180" optional="true"/>
  <recv response="200" rtd="true" rrs="true"/>

  <send>
    <![CDATA[
      ACK [next_url] SIP/2.0
      Via: SIP/2.0/[transport] [local_ip]:[local_port];branch=[branch];rport
      [routes]
      From: sipp <sip:sipp@[local_ip]:[local_port]>;tag=[pid]SIPpTag00[call_number]
      To: sut <sip:[service]@[remote_ip]:[remote_port]>[peer_tag_param]
      Call-ID: [call_id]
      CSeq: 1 ACK
      Contact: sip:sipp@[local_ip]:[local_port]
      Max-Forwards: 70
      Content-Length: 0
    ]]>
  </send>

  <!-- OPTIONS-driven hold: reply 200 to EVERY keepalive, forever, then
       loop back. The recv is MANDATORY (no optional=true) — sipp rejects
       an `optional=true recv` immediately followed by a `<send>`. With
       `ontimeout` set, mandatory recv jumps to the labeled step instead
       of aborting on timeout — so the call ends ONLY when keepalives stop
       arriving for `timeout` ms (B2BUA terminated the call, chaos event,
       network failure) → exit to the BYE phase.

       There is deliberately NO per-call OPTIONS cap. An earlier revision
       capped the loop at 4 iterations (UAC sends its own BYE after ~20 min)
       to bound sipp's CurrentCall growth, but that cap CORRUPTED the
       reboot-survival measurement: once a call passed its 4th OPTIONS it
       left this recv, so the rebooted worker's smoothed keepalive-replay
       burst (router::reclaim_all) landed OPTIONS on a UAC no longer parked
       here → sipp scored them OutOfCallMsgs and aborted the call with
       `unexpected_msg`, which read as a (false) ~130% long-call loss across
       every reboot even though the server's reclaim was 100% complete and
       correctly routed. A real UAC answers in-dialog OPTIONS for the life
       of the call, so this models reality AND removes the artifact: a
       reclaimed dialog's replayed OPTIONS always lands on a parked recv and
       is answered. CurrentCall growth is bounded operationally by the job's
       `-l MAX_CONCURRENT` ceiling + `-recv_timeout` dead-call reaper
       (manifests/40-sipp-uac-job.yaml), not by a per-call message count. -->
  <label id="hold_loop"/>
  <recv request="OPTIONS" crlf="true" timeout="420000" ontimeout="end_hold"/>
  <send>
    <![CDATA[
      SIP/2.0 200 OK
      [last_Via:]
      [last_Record-Route:]
      [last_From:]
      [last_To:]
      [last_Call-ID:]
      [last_CSeq:]
      Contact: sip:sipp@[local_ip]:[local_port]
      Content-Length: 0
    ]]>
  </send>
  <nop next="hold_loop"/>

  <label id="end_hold"/>
  <send retrans="500">
    <![CDATA[
      BYE [next_url] SIP/2.0
      Via: SIP/2.0/[transport] [local_ip]:[local_port];branch=[branch];rport
      [routes]
      From: sipp <sip:sipp@[local_ip]:[local_port]>;tag=[pid]SIPpTag00[call_number]
      To: sut <sip:[service]@[remote_ip]:[remote_port]>[peer_tag_param]
      Call-ID: [call_id]
      CSeq: 2 BYE
      Contact: sip:sipp@[local_ip]:[local_port]
      Max-Forwards: 70
      Content-Length: 0
    ]]>
  </send>

  <recv response="200" crlf="true"/>

  <ResponseTimeRepartition value="10, 20, 30, 40, 50, 100, 150, 200"/>
  <CallLengthRepartition value="60000, 300000, 600000, 900000, 1200000"/>
</scenario>
